==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|pleden}}, {{m|enm|plaiden}}, from {{der|en|fro|plaider||to plead, offer a plea}}, from {{m|fro|plait}}, from {{der|en|ML.|placitum||a decree, sentence, suit, plea, etc.", in Classical {{der|en|la|-}}, "an opinion, determination, prescription, order; literally, that which is pleasing, pleasure}}, neuter of {{m|la|placitus}}, past participle of {{m|la|placeō||to please}}. Cognate with {{cog|es|pleitear||to litigate, take to court}}.

