===Verb===
{{en-verb|pleads|pleading|pleaded|past_qual=North America, England, legal|past2=pled|past2_qual=North America, Scotland|past3=plead|past3_qual=North America}}

# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To present (an argument or a plea), especially in a legal case.
#: {{ux|en|The defendant has decided to '''plead''' not guilty.}}
#* Bible, Job xvi. 21
#*: O that one might '''plead''' for a man with God, as a man '''pleadeth''' for his neighbour!
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To beg, beseech, or implore.
#: {{ux|en|He '''pleaded''' with me not to leave the house.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To offer by way of [[excuse]].
#: ''Not wishing to attend the banquet, I '''pleaded''' illness.''
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[discuss]] by [[argument]]s.

